{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"1bfe22e3-87b2-5231-878d-b3d1b4bff5cb","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 4ee71fb8-509a-430a-ba06-a7f20188ee08 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 4ee71fb8-509a-430a-ba06-a7f20188ee08 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 9c9505bc-2c1d-4b3e-a970-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field faa461c0-695b-47ab-90f5-a7f20188ee08 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field faa461c0-695b-47ab-90f5-a7f20188ee08 --><!-- begin field c9982659-49c0-4f31-ad41-a7f20188ee08 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field c9982659-49c0-4f31-ad41-a7f20188ee08 --><!-- begin field f1484daa-3661-4a13-ad00-a7f20188ee08 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field f1484daa-3661-4a13-ad00-a7f20188ee08 --><!-- begin field ae54cd19-15de-4ac0-8beb-a7f20188ee08 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field ae54cd19-15de-4ac0-8beb-a7f20188ee08 --><!-- begin field acf6e872-1317-4174-af91-a7f20188ee08 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field acf6e872-1317-4174-af91-a7f20188ee08 --><!-- begin field 441aedbb-b87f-4f55-826b-a7f20188ee08 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 441aedbb-b87f-4f55-826b-a7f20188ee08 --><!-- end item 9c9505bc-2c1d-4b3e-a970-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"d5cf1db6-a6d9-54fb-b393-095d8af57067","topicId":"9042b194-f66e-44c6-a91c-76ffa626e3e8","topicName":"Diarrhoea - prevention and advice for travellers","slug":"diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers","lastRevised":"Last revised in February 2019","chapters":[{"id":"3f7bee04-88e6-5a40-86d5-e39dc29e4059","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"47ddb819-f046-5e92-999c-a3d47a00ede8","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"bdd3d81e-da2b-5807-b257-8dd4d73a596c","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"5ac4ad9d-b3fb-51c6-84de-19181b30e02c","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"5568a30c-164d-5d4f-8d41-ad7eff1173cb","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"6f04e901-40c5-5906-a7eb-5935a99758bb","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"e0f32109-cb0a-51e3-aa59-bcac4a364a5f","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"4a74f052-b6c8-5743-b69f-30ffc630174e","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id